3
00:01:50,340 --> 00:01:52,010
Red Leg Zeff.

4
00:01:52,630 --> 00:01:55,140
You're alive.

5
00:01:55,140 --> 00:01:59,600
No pirate could compare to you,
being both a cook and a captain...

6
00:02:00,100 --> 00:02:02,810
I'm alive. So what?

7
00:02:02,810 --> 00:02:05,480
It's none of your concern.

8
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:10,070
As you can see, I'm passing
my time as a cook now.

9
00:02:12,900 --> 00:02:15,700
It sounds better
when you say it like that...

10
00:02:15,700 --> 00:02:19,540
but you're not just
passing time as a cook.

11
00:02:19,540 --> 00:02:22,710
it looks like you can only
pass your time as a cook.

12
00:02:23,120 --> 00:02:30,210
Red Leg Zeff was a master of kicks
who never used his hands in battle.

13
00:02:30,630 --> 00:02:37,970
His mighty legs were said to shatter
bedrock and even leave footprints in steel.

14
00:02:38,760 --> 00:02:40,680
And "Red Leg" referred to your boots,

15
00:02:40,680 --> 00:02:46,690
washed in the blood of those
you kicked into submission.

16
00:02:47,440 --> 00:02:52,440
But you seem to have lost
one of your precious legs...

17
00:02:53,490 --> 00:02:56,200
I guess the rumors were true.

18
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:59,530
A stroke of bad luck
doomed you to an accident at sea.

19
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:06,250
I suppose losing a leg would mean
you've lost the ability to fight.

20
00:03:06,580 --> 00:03:08,920
I don't give a damn about fighting.

21
00:03:08,920 --> 00:03:13,670
I may have lost a leg, but I can cook
so long as I have these two hands.

22
00:03:13,670 --> 00:03:17,470
Whatever it is, get to
the damn point already!

23
00:03:19,140 --> 00:03:21,180
Red Leg Zeff,

24
00:03:21,180 --> 00:03:26,480
you once sailed the Grand Line
and returned unscathed.

25
00:03:26,480 --> 00:03:32,570
You must have the logbook
from that year-long voyage.

26
00:03:32,980 --> 00:03:34,360
Hand it over!

27
00:03:35,950 --> 00:03:40,160
Wow, Boss Man!
You sailed the Grand Line, too?!

28
00:03:40,160 --> 00:03:41,160
I did...

29
00:03:41,990 --> 00:03:43,660
My logbook, huh?

30
00:03:43,660 --> 00:03:47,210
Sure, I've got what you're looking for.

31
00:03:47,620 --> 00:03:50,290
But there's no way in hell
I'm giving it to you.

32
00:03:51,500 --> 00:03:56,720
That logbook is the pride
of all those who sailed with me.

33
00:03:56,720 --> 00:04:01,260
The likes of you
couldn't even handle it.

34
00:04:01,720 --> 00:04:04,310
Then I'll just have to take it!

35
00:04:05,060 --> 00:04:08,560
I admit the Grand Line
got the better of me.

36
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:12,320
That being said, I'm still
the indomitable Don Krieg...

37
00:04:12,980 --> 00:04:16,990
and I had the power necessary
to cross such a treacherous sea.

38
00:04:16,990 --> 00:04:18,200
I had the men.

39
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:19,660
I had the ambition.

40
00:04:21,490 --> 00:04:25,410
The only thing I lacked
was information.

41
00:04:25,870 --> 00:04:28,120
I just didn't know what to expect.

42
00:04:29,210 --> 00:04:31,630
I will have that logbook.

43
00:04:31,630 --> 00:04:37,340
With it, I will reassemble
my pirate fleet, seize the One Piece,

44
00:04:37,760 --> 00:04:41,140
and rise to the top
of this Great Pirate Era!

45
00:04:46,770 --> 00:04:47,850
Wait just a minute.

46
00:04:48,230 --> 00:04:50,600
I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!

47
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:52,270
Cabin Boy?!

48
00:04:53,520 --> 00:04:56,030
Hey, back down, Cabin Boy!

49
00:04:56,030 --> 00:04:57,900
You're no match for him!

50
00:04:57,900 --> 00:05:00,610
I can't back down. Not about this.

51
00:05:02,530 --> 00:05:05,160
Did you say something, kid?

52
00:05:05,660 --> 00:05:08,000
We can pretend
I didn't hear you say that.

53
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:10,080
No need to pretend.

54
00:05:10,080 --> 00:05:12,000
I'm only stating the facts.

55
00:05:12,790 --> 00:05:15,000
This is no game, boy.

56
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:16,630
Of course not.

57
00:05:16,630 --> 00:05:18,970
I will conquer the Grand Line.

58
00:05:19,760 --> 00:05:21,760
It's no joke, you brat!

59
00:05:21,760 --> 00:05:23,890
Putting aside what we didn't know,

60
00:05:23,890 --> 00:05:27,850
our fleet of 5,000 sailors only lasted
seven days on that devilish sea!

61
00:05:27,850 --> 00:05:30,060
A kid like you doesn't stand a chance!

62
00:05:30,060 --> 00:05:32,060
S-Seven days?!

63
00:05:32,060 --> 00:05:34,940
The Krieg Pirates only
lasted seven days?!

64
00:05:35,610 --> 00:05:37,280
What the hell happened to them?!

65
00:05:37,860 --> 00:05:42,030
I'm sorry, but I hate it
when people joke around like this.

66
00:05:42,530 --> 00:05:47,490
If you persist, I'll just
crush you right here and now.

67
00:05:47,910 --> 00:05:49,870
If you can.

68
00:05:52,500 --> 00:05:54,330
Perfect.

69
00:05:54,330 --> 00:05:58,380
As you wish, I'll be
sending you to the afterlife.

70
00:06:04,220 --> 00:06:06,930
Gonna fight, Luffy? Need a hand?

71
00:06:06,930 --> 00:06:09,470
A-And if you don't need help,
th-that's fine too...

72
00:06:10,140 --> 00:06:13,140
Zoro! Usopp! I didn't see you there!

73
00:06:13,140 --> 00:06:15,230
I'm fine. Just watch from there.

74
00:06:15,230 --> 00:06:16,520
I-If you insist!

75
00:06:18,610 --> 00:06:21,110
Are those your men?

76
00:06:21,690 --> 00:06:24,160
Don't you think
your crew is a bit small?!

77
00:06:24,160 --> 00:06:27,070
What're you talking about?!
We have two more!

78
00:06:27,070 --> 00:06:29,040
Hey! You counted me, didn't you?!

79
00:06:30,450 --> 00:06:32,790
I'll deal with you later.

80
00:06:33,330 --> 00:06:36,290
I'm going to feed my men first.

81
00:06:38,960 --> 00:06:44,010
Anyone who wants to live
should clear out before I get back.

82
00:06:44,760 --> 00:06:49,180
I'm only after your
logbook and this ship.

83
00:06:50,930 --> 00:06:54,690
If you still want
to throw your life away,

84
00:06:54,690 --> 00:06:57,860
I'll spare some time
to bury you at sea!

85
00:06:58,360 --> 00:06:59,980
Make your choice.

86
00:07:04,740 --> 00:07:06,740
I'm so sorry, Sanji.

87
00:07:06,740 --> 00:07:09,580
I had no idea he'd go this far.

88
00:07:09,580 --> 00:07:13,410
You don't need to apologize, grunt.

89
00:07:14,580 --> 00:07:18,920
Every cook here did
what they thought was right.

90
00:07:18,920 --> 00:07:21,000
That's all there is to it.

91
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,380
Chef Zeff!

92
00:07:22,380 --> 00:07:27,010
You're not seriously taking
Sanji's side in this, are you?

93
00:07:27,010 --> 00:07:28,340
That's right!

94
00:07:28,340 --> 00:07:31,220
It's his fault this happened!

95
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:34,770
He's trying to destroy
your precious restaurant!

96
00:07:34,770 --> 00:07:36,560
Shut up, you damn eggplants!

97
00:07:37,770 --> 00:07:43,780
Have you ever felt such hunger
you thought you'd die?!

98
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:51,280
Can you comprehend the terror of running
out of food and water on this vast ocean?!

99
00:07:51,280 --> 00:07:54,540
Can you comprehend such suffering?!

100
00:07:54,540 --> 00:07:55,410
Huh?

101
00:07:55,410 --> 00:07:58,040
Ch-Chef Zeff, what do you mean?

102
00:07:58,040 --> 00:08:00,580
If all you're going to do
is bitch and moan,

103
00:08:00,580 --> 00:08:03,550
crawl out the back door and get lost!

104
00:08:05,670 --> 00:08:08,300
I'll stay and fight.

105
00:08:08,300 --> 00:08:11,470
I'm too pissed off to let
myself get whupped like that!

106
00:08:11,470 --> 00:08:15,430
I'm staying too! This is
where I work after all!

107
00:08:15,430 --> 00:08:17,810
We have nowhere else to go anyway!

108
00:08:19,650 --> 00:08:21,690
What are you doing?!

109
00:08:21,690 --> 00:08:24,650
You saw what the don is capable of!

110
00:08:24,650 --> 00:08:26,150
Hey, Gin!

111
00:08:26,570 --> 00:08:28,110
Let me tell you something.

112
00:08:28,110 --> 00:08:33,080
My duty as a cook is to feed
those who are hungry.

113
00:08:33,080 --> 00:08:33,870
That said...

114
00:08:38,660 --> 00:08:42,040
when those looters
turn on me with full bellies...

115
00:08:42,790 --> 00:08:47,630
I don't want to hear you complain
when I beat up your fellow pirates.

116
00:08:47,630 --> 00:08:49,550
Just try to take this restaurant,

117
00:08:49,880 --> 00:08:53,260
and I'll kill you without
a second thought.

118
00:08:53,890 --> 00:08:55,010
Understood?

119
00:08:57,220 --> 00:09:01,650
You'd kill him after saving his life?
You're hopeless, Sanji...

120
00:09:01,650 --> 00:09:03,060
Shut up, you crappy cook!

121
00:09:03,440 --> 00:09:05,690
See? He's pretty cool, huh?!

122
00:09:05,690 --> 00:09:08,110
That's nice, but enough about him!

123
00:09:08,110 --> 00:09:10,240
We have to get out of here!

124
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:11,160
Settle down!

125
00:09:11,700 --> 00:09:14,660
He may be Krieg,
but he's in bad shape.

126
00:09:15,660 --> 00:09:20,330
Gin, you said you don't know anything
about the Grand Line, didn't you?

127
00:09:20,330 --> 00:09:22,210
But you've been there.

128
00:09:23,330 --> 00:09:25,670
I still don't know a thing
about the Grand Line.

129
00:09:26,130 --> 00:09:30,340
What we saw on our
seventh day on the Grand Line...

130
00:09:30,340 --> 00:09:32,010
I don't know if it was a dream...

131
00:09:33,090 --> 00:09:34,050
or reality...

132
00:09:35,050 --> 00:09:38,890
I still can't wrap my head around it.

133
00:09:39,850 --> 00:09:41,640
It was unbelievable!

134
00:09:44,060 --> 00:09:45,770
How could a lone man...

135
00:09:48,280 --> 00:09:51,990
destroy a fleet of fifty ships?!

136
00:09:56,870 --> 00:09:59,620
– What?!
– What?!

137
00:10:01,410 --> 00:10:04,250
It happened out of nowhere.

138
00:10:04,250 --> 00:10:07,630
Before we even realized he was there,

139
00:10:07,630 --> 00:10:10,670
the ships began to sink,
one after another.

140
00:10:15,010 --> 00:10:18,510
If we hadn't been lucky enough
to encounter that storm,

141
00:10:18,510 --> 00:10:21,810
our flagship would have
met the same fate.

142
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:33,570
I don't know how many
of our ships survived.

143
00:10:33,570 --> 00:10:38,200
It's just too horrible
to believe it was real.

144
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:40,160
I want to forget what happened!

145
00:10:41,160 --> 00:10:42,910
I want to forget that man—

146
00:10:42,910 --> 00:10:46,830
how he could seemingly kill
with just a glance—

147
00:10:46,830 --> 00:10:49,170
with that hawk-like glare!

148
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:50,800
What?!

149
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:51,550
Huh?

150
00:10:52,670 --> 00:10:54,470
Could it be...?!

151
00:10:58,180 --> 00:11:00,260
There's no mistaking it.

152
00:11:00,680 --> 00:11:04,020
That must be the man
known as Hawk Eye.

153
00:11:04,020 --> 00:11:04,890
What?

154
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:11,360
Just telling us that his eyes were like
those of a hawk wouldn't be proof alone.

155
00:11:11,360 --> 00:11:17,490
But knowing he was capable of something
so devastating is plenty convincing for me.

156
00:11:17,950 --> 00:11:19,830
The hawk-eyed man!

157
00:11:19,830 --> 00:11:22,160
Huh? Do you know him, Zoro?

158
00:11:23,410 --> 00:11:25,040
Yeah...

159
00:11:25,040 --> 00:11:27,330
It's who I've been looking for.

160
00:11:29,420 --> 00:11:33,340
Is it possible he had some sort
of grudge against your crew?

161
00:11:33,340 --> 00:11:35,220
I'd never seen him before!

162
00:11:35,220 --> 00:11:38,010
Maybe you woke him
from a nap or something.

163
00:11:38,010 --> 00:11:39,640
Don't be ridiculous!

164
00:11:39,640 --> 00:11:42,890
Who the hell smashes
an entire fleet over that?!

165
00:11:44,230 --> 00:11:46,140
Don't get so worked up.

166
00:11:46,140 --> 00:11:47,850
It's just an example.

167
00:11:48,650 --> 00:11:53,820
That is, it's an example of what
kind of place the Grand Line is.

168
00:11:53,820 --> 00:11:56,450
What kind of place is that?!

169
00:11:56,450 --> 00:11:59,200
A place where anything could happen.

170
00:12:00,370 --> 00:12:03,620
Hey Luffy, we shouldn't
go somewhere like that!

171
00:12:03,620 --> 00:12:05,250
Luffy!

172
00:12:08,250 --> 00:12:10,170
Hey, Luffy?

173
00:12:10,540 --> 00:12:13,920
Whoa, that's so freaking cool!

174
00:12:13,920 --> 00:12:15,970
I knew it had to be crazy there!

175
00:12:15,970 --> 00:12:18,510
At least acknowledge
how dangerous it is!

176
00:12:18,510 --> 00:12:23,260
Well, that settles it. My only goal
at this point is the Grand Line.

177
00:12:23,260 --> 00:12:24,720
What?!

178
00:12:25,140 --> 00:12:26,770
I'll find him there...

179
00:12:26,770 --> 00:12:29,600
I'll find that man on the Grand Line!

180
00:12:31,230 --> 00:12:33,440
Are you nuts?

181
00:12:34,150 --> 00:12:36,610
You're the type
to charge in and die first.

182
00:12:36,990 --> 00:12:40,450
You're right, but saying I'm "nuts" is going too far.

183
00:12:41,570 --> 00:12:46,410
I threw my life away when I decided
to be the world's greatest swordsman.

184
00:12:46,910 --> 00:12:51,130
Only one person can call me nuts,
and that person is me!

185
00:12:53,290 --> 00:12:55,630
Yeah, the same goes for me!

186
00:12:55,630 --> 00:12:58,380
Yeah, me too, since I'm
a man of the sea and all!

187
00:12:58,380 --> 00:13:00,090
In your case, that's a lie.

188
00:13:02,550 --> 00:13:04,310
Ridiculous...

189
00:13:07,730 --> 00:13:09,730
Hey, hey!

190
00:13:09,730 --> 00:13:13,730
Do you numbskulls have any idea
what's going on here?!

191
00:13:13,730 --> 00:13:20,950
Outside this restaurant is a massive galleon
from Pirate Commodore Don Krieg's fleet!

192
00:13:20,950 --> 00:13:25,030
You can build your castles in the sky
when the battle is over!

193
00:13:34,170 --> 00:13:36,550
– We're saved!
– We're saved!

194
00:13:36,550 --> 00:13:38,300
This is great! We're gonna live!

195
00:13:38,300 --> 00:13:39,840
It's like I'm dreaming!

196
00:13:39,840 --> 00:13:42,510
We're free from that nightmare!

197
00:13:42,510 --> 00:13:46,970
We made it back alive
from the Pirate Graveyard!

198
00:13:49,060 --> 00:13:50,140
That's right...

199
00:13:50,890 --> 00:13:55,230
We can once again turn
our sights on the Grand Line.

200
00:13:57,900 --> 00:13:59,360
Huh?

201
00:13:59,360 --> 00:14:00,990
What's with those looks?

202
00:14:01,570 --> 00:14:03,910
W-We're going back there?!

203
00:14:09,830 --> 00:14:13,580
Any other objections?

204
00:14:25,550 --> 00:14:26,800
First,

205
00:14:27,350 --> 00:14:32,520
we'll abandon this irreparable wreck
and take over the restaurant.

206
00:14:32,520 --> 00:14:35,690
Our enemy is a staff of punk cooks.

207
00:14:35,690 --> 00:14:38,270
They've got nothing on us.

208
00:14:44,490 --> 00:14:45,780
Attack!

209
00:14:51,250 --> 00:14:53,710
They're coming!
I can hear them yelling!

210
00:14:53,710 --> 00:14:57,750
Hold them off! This ship—
this restaurant is ours!

211
00:15:01,380 --> 00:15:03,130
Make way, you scum!

212
00:15:19,650 --> 00:15:20,520
What was that?!

213
00:15:21,860 --> 00:15:23,360
What happened?!

214
00:15:23,360 --> 00:15:25,320
Don Krieg!

215
00:15:25,320 --> 00:15:27,280
Our flagship was...

216
00:15:27,280 --> 00:15:29,280
sliced in half!

217
00:15:29,280 --> 00:15:32,040
Sliced in half?! Did I hear that right?!

218
00:15:32,040 --> 00:15:34,790
Our massive galleon?!

219
00:15:34,790 --> 00:15:35,910
How could...

220
00:15:36,500 --> 00:15:40,750
something so preposterous happen?!

221
00:15:43,960 --> 00:15:45,720
Weigh anchor!

222
00:15:45,720 --> 00:15:47,970
It'll bring the whole ship down!

223
00:15:47,970 --> 00:15:48,930
Yes, sir!

224
00:15:51,430 --> 00:15:52,430
Not good!

225
00:15:52,430 --> 00:15:55,390
Nami, Yosaku, and Johnny
are on the ship out front!

226
00:15:56,480 --> 00:15:59,060
Dammit! It's probably too late!

227
00:16:07,860 --> 00:16:09,950
Big Bro!

228
00:16:09,950 --> 00:16:11,410
Big Bro!

229
00:16:11,410 --> 00:16:14,410
Yosaku! Johnny!

230
00:16:14,410 --> 00:16:15,410
Are you guys okay?

231
00:16:15,790 --> 00:16:18,540
Where's the ship?! It's gone!
What happened to Nami?!

232
00:16:18,540 --> 00:16:19,790
Well...

233
00:16:19,790 --> 00:16:23,460
I'm sorry, Big Bro! She's already gone!

234
00:16:23,460 --> 00:16:26,050
See ya! Tell Luffy and his crew...

235
00:16:26,050 --> 00:16:27,550
Big Sis Nami...!

236
00:16:27,550 --> 00:16:30,140
"If fate allows, let's meet again!"

237
00:16:30,930 --> 00:16:34,890
She took all the treasure and ran off!

238
00:16:34,890 --> 00:16:36,100
– Wha...?!
– Wha...?!

239
00:16:36,100 --> 00:16:38,230
– What did you say?!
– What did you say?!

240
00:16:50,490 --> 00:16:52,160
That man...

241
00:17:09,840 --> 00:17:10,840
What'd you say?!

242
00:17:10,840 --> 00:17:14,100
Nami ran off with the Going Merry?!

243
00:17:14,100 --> 00:17:16,390
What the hell is she doing?!

244
00:17:22,060 --> 00:17:25,110
It happened just a moment ago!

245
00:17:29,240 --> 00:17:31,490
What's the matter, Big Sis Nami?

246
00:17:31,490 --> 00:17:32,070
Huh?

247
00:17:32,660 --> 00:17:35,200
What's with the wanted posters?

248
00:17:35,200 --> 00:17:37,200
Ah... It's nothing.

249
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:39,450
You just continue to impress.

250
00:17:39,870 --> 00:17:42,580
I see a big bounty
has caught your eye.

251
00:17:42,580 --> 00:17:46,460
But I'll tell you that Arlong's
the one pirate to steer clear of.

252
00:17:46,460 --> 00:17:48,550
They say he's freakishly strong.

253
00:17:48,550 --> 00:17:52,630
He had been laying low for a while...

254
00:17:52,630 --> 00:17:55,600
...but he started making
waves again recently.

255
00:17:55,970 --> 00:17:59,520
Though it's hard to resist that
20-million-berry bounty,

256
00:17:59,520 --> 00:18:05,730
this guy's so strong that even we might
be a hair's width from death if we fought.

257
00:18:06,320 --> 00:18:07,020
– Huh?
– Huh?

258
00:18:07,400 --> 00:18:08,440
Big Sis Nami?

259
00:18:10,070 --> 00:18:14,280
So sorry, but can you turn around?
I need to get changed.

260
00:18:14,280 --> 00:18:15,280
– What?!
– What?!

261
00:18:15,280 --> 00:18:16,910
W-Well...

262
00:18:16,910 --> 00:18:18,240
Change? Here? Now?!

263
00:18:18,790 --> 00:18:20,450
If you don't mind.

264
00:18:21,080 --> 00:18:22,790
– Please go ahead!
– Please go ahead!

265
00:18:27,750 --> 00:18:30,760
She's as bold as she looks!

266
00:18:30,760 --> 00:18:33,680
It wouldn't hurt if we took
a quick peek, would it?

267
00:18:33,680 --> 00:18:34,470
Not one bit!

268
00:18:41,810 --> 00:18:43,600
Wh-What are you doing?!

269
00:18:44,730 --> 00:18:46,940
What am I doing?
Just a little business.

270
00:18:46,940 --> 00:18:49,070
I'm a thief who steals from pirates.

271
00:18:49,070 --> 00:18:50,730
I'll be taking the ship now.

272
00:18:51,690 --> 00:18:54,820
I never said that
I was a member of their crew.

273
00:18:54,820 --> 00:18:56,280
It was just an alliance.

274
00:18:56,280 --> 00:19:01,040
I only spent a short time with Luffy
and his pals, but I had a lot of fun.

275
00:19:01,910 --> 00:19:03,540
Tell them this:

276
00:19:04,410 --> 00:19:07,290
"If fate allows, let's meet again."

277
00:19:08,540 --> 00:19:10,460
Big Sis Nami!

278
00:19:17,840 --> 00:19:20,180
W-Wait! You can't do that!

279
00:19:20,180 --> 00:19:25,060
We were supposed to
keep watch of the ship!

280
00:19:30,400 --> 00:19:33,740
And that's how the ship
got taken away...

281
00:19:33,740 --> 00:19:34,570
We're sorry!

282
00:19:34,570 --> 00:19:35,400
Dammit!

283
00:19:35,400 --> 00:19:38,780
Just when things couldn't
get any worse...!

284
00:19:38,780 --> 00:19:41,120
Kaya gave us that ship!

285
00:19:41,120 --> 00:19:43,080
Wait! I can still see it!

286
00:19:43,080 --> 00:19:45,040
It's the Going Merry!

287
00:19:45,410 --> 00:19:46,790
Where's your ship?

288
00:19:46,790 --> 00:19:48,380
We still have it here...

289
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:50,630
Zoro! Usopp! Get going!

290
00:19:50,630 --> 00:19:52,590
Take their ship and follow Nami!

291
00:19:52,590 --> 00:19:55,420
Forget about it.
Just let her have the ship.

292
00:19:55,420 --> 00:19:58,140
We're better off
not going after that woman.

293
00:19:58,140 --> 00:20:01,010
I won't accept anyone
but her as our navigator!

294
00:20:03,430 --> 00:20:06,940
Fine, have it your way...
What a high-maintenance captain.

295
00:20:07,520 --> 00:20:08,690
Hey, Usopp! Let's go!

296
00:20:08,690 --> 00:20:10,230
O-Okay...

297
00:20:12,270 --> 00:20:14,820
– Big Bro Zoro, the ship is ready!
– Big Bro Zoro, the ship is ready!

298
00:20:15,190 --> 00:20:16,570
Luffy, what about you?

299
00:20:16,570 --> 00:20:20,820
I can't go until I settle things
here at the restaurant.

300
00:20:20,820 --> 00:20:22,280
Be careful.

301
00:20:22,280 --> 00:20:24,620
There's something fishy going on here.

302
00:20:24,620 --> 00:20:26,580
Yeah, I can tell.

303
00:20:26,580 --> 00:20:29,500
The ship's been split in half!

304
00:20:30,380 --> 00:20:31,710
Look! Over there!

305
00:20:32,380 --> 00:20:33,800
I-I-It's him!

306
00:20:38,930 --> 00:20:42,100
Don Krieg! It's that man!

307
00:20:42,100 --> 00:20:45,470
It's the man who destroyed our fleet!

308
00:20:48,520 --> 00:20:51,060
Th-That man...

309
00:20:59,820 --> 00:21:01,360
He's the one that...

310
00:21:03,070 --> 00:21:05,660
That damn mangy cur!

311
00:21:06,330 --> 00:21:08,370
He chased us all the way here...

312
00:21:08,370 --> 00:21:10,460
to kill us!

313
00:21:10,920 --> 00:21:12,630
We're screwed!

314
00:21:13,380 --> 00:21:14,250
Zoro?

315
00:21:14,840 --> 00:21:16,210
Who's that?

316
00:21:16,920 --> 00:21:19,420
The man I've been looking for.

317
00:21:19,930 --> 00:21:21,840
Hawk Eye Mihawk!

318
00:21:22,760 --> 00:21:25,010
Hawk Eye Mihawk...

319
00:21:31,350 --> 00:21:33,360
The world's greatest...

320
00:21:35,320 --> 00:21:41,910
So he's the one who single-handedly
sank Krieg's fifty ships in the Grand Line?

321
00:21:41,910 --> 00:21:45,620
Then, he must be the one
who just obliterated Krieg's ship.

322
00:21:45,620 --> 00:21:49,410
He looks just like
an ordinary person, though!

323
00:21:49,410 --> 00:21:52,420
He doesn't seem to have
any special weapons either.

324
00:21:53,040 --> 00:21:54,920
His weapon is on his back...

325
00:21:54,920 --> 00:21:57,340
You're kidding!

326
00:21:57,340 --> 00:22:01,220
Did he really carve up that
massive ship using just his sword?!

327
00:22:01,720 --> 00:22:04,850
He's the master swordsman Hawk Eye,

328
00:22:04,850 --> 00:22:08,680
the man who stands at the top
of the world of swordsmen.

329
00:22:13,270 --> 00:22:15,270
Y-You son of a bitch...

330
00:22:15,770 --> 00:22:18,780
What kind of grudge would
make you chase us this far?

331
00:22:20,110 --> 00:22:21,440
Just killing time.

332
00:22:21,440 --> 00:22:25,370
Wha...?! Don't mock us!

333
00:22:34,960 --> 00:22:36,210
Wh-What?!

334
00:22:36,590 --> 00:22:38,380
I'm sure I aimed straight for him!

335
00:22:38,380 --> 00:22:39,710
He diverted the bullets.

336
00:22:40,460 --> 00:22:43,720
He gently changed their course
with just the tip of his sword.

337
00:22:44,180 --> 00:22:45,550
That's ridiculous!

338
00:22:46,720 --> 00:22:49,100
H-Hey! Who are you?!

339
00:22:49,430 --> 00:22:53,140
I've never seen someone
wield their sword so delicately.

340
00:22:53,810 --> 00:22:56,690
Swordplay that relies on force
is void of power.

341
00:22:57,230 --> 00:23:00,190
Did you use that sword
to slice up this ship as well?

342
00:23:00,190 --> 00:23:01,650
Correct.

343
00:23:01,650 --> 00:23:03,070
I see why...

344
00:23:03,530 --> 00:23:04,820
you're the greatest...

345
00:23:04,820 --> 00:23:07,700
Three swords... Could he be...?!

346
00:23:07,700 --> 00:23:11,160
I set out to sea in order to meet you.

347
00:23:11,160 --> 00:23:12,830
What's your goal?

348
00:23:12,830 --> 00:23:14,290
To become the greatest!

349
00:23:15,580 --> 00:23:17,080
How foolish...

350
00:23:34,350 --> 00:23:36,310
They were nice guys...

351
00:23:36,310 --> 00:23:40,730
I wonder if they'll let me rejoin them
if we ever meet again.

352
00:23:42,440 --> 00:23:44,650
Will we ever meet again?

353
00:23:46,280 --> 00:23:48,820
I want to be free...

354
00:23:51,120 --> 00:23:52,990
Bell-mère...

355
00:23:57,420 --> 00:24:00,290
You have time to kill,
right? Let's fight!

356
00:24:00,290 --> 00:24:03,460
Th-This guy is... Zoro!

357
00:24:03,460 --> 00:24:05,670
Roronoa Zoro of the three-sword style!

358
00:24:05,670 --> 00:24:06,630
What?!

359
00:24:07,880 --> 00:24:09,260
The Pirate Hunter, huh?

360
00:24:10,140 --> 00:24:11,680
That's who he is?!

361
00:24:14,890 --> 00:24:16,890
Hey, we've got a problem, Luffy!

362
00:24:16,890 --> 00:24:19,440
The Going Merry
will be out of sight soon!

363
00:24:19,440 --> 00:24:20,900
Hey, Luffy!

364
00:24:21,270 --> 00:24:22,570
Fight?

365
00:24:23,690 --> 00:24:26,070
I pity you, child.

366
00:24:30,530 --> 00:24:32,370
If you are a competent swordsman,

367
00:24:32,370 --> 00:24:37,410
you must see the disparity in our abilities
without the need to cross swords.

368
00:24:37,790 --> 00:24:40,670
What compels you
to bare your fangs at me?

369
00:24:40,670 --> 00:24:44,500
Is it courage, or is it ignorance?

370
00:24:44,500 --> 00:24:46,760
It's my ambition!

371
00:24:49,380 --> 00:24:52,390
And a promise I made to a dear friend.

372
00:24:52,390 --> 00:24:56,020
H-Hawk Eye Mihawk,
the world's greatest swordsman,

373
00:24:56,020 --> 00:24:58,060
and Pirate Hunter Zoro...

374
00:24:58,060 --> 00:25:00,650
What kind of fight will it be?

375
00:25:01,060 --> 00:25:03,650
There's no one out there
who can defeat Big Bro!

376
00:25:03,650 --> 00:25:04,400
Y-Yeah!

377
00:25:04,730 --> 00:25:06,860
Big Bro is already the strongest!

378
00:25:11,110 --> 00:25:13,990
Hey, what are you
planning to do with that?

379
00:25:14,490 --> 00:25:18,960
I'm not some brute
who hunts rabbits with a cannon.

380
00:25:18,960 --> 00:25:22,170
Even if you're a swordsman
of some renown,

381
00:25:22,170 --> 00:25:27,920
this sea, the East Blue,
is the weakest among the four seas.

382
00:25:28,380 --> 00:25:32,260
Unfortunately, this is
the smallest blade on my person.

383
00:25:32,260 --> 00:25:35,810
Stop underestimating me!

384
00:25:35,810 --> 00:25:38,100
Better not regret it when I kill you!

385
00:25:38,100 --> 00:25:39,480
Frog in the well...

386
00:25:39,480 --> 00:25:41,440
learn just how big this world is.

387
00:25:41,440 --> 00:25:43,350
Oni Giri!

388
00:25:46,570 --> 00:25:48,610
Wh-What?!

389
00:25:53,910 --> 00:25:55,080
Zoro?!

390
00:25:55,450 --> 00:25:58,580
How...? Big Bro's
Oni Giri was stopped!

391
00:25:58,580 --> 00:26:02,040
His big finisher never fails
to blow away his enemies, but it...!

392
00:26:02,040 --> 00:26:03,790
What's going on?!

393
00:26:04,330 --> 00:26:08,250
I... I can't move them!
What did he do?!

394
00:26:08,250 --> 00:26:12,510
This move lands every time,
but he stopped it using this toy?!

395
00:26:13,010 --> 00:26:15,470
This... can't be happening!

396
00:26:16,640 --> 00:26:19,060
This is the difference in our abilities?!

397
00:26:19,060 --> 00:26:22,060
That can't be right!
There's no way it's that far...!

398
00:26:24,560 --> 00:26:27,190
I can't be this far behind the world!

399
00:26:35,120 --> 00:26:37,990
This can't be happening, right,
Big Bro?! Get serious!

400
00:26:37,990 --> 00:26:39,700
Big Bro!

401
00:26:39,700 --> 00:26:42,080
This distance between us can't be real!

402
00:26:56,050 --> 00:26:58,140
Such heavy-handed swordplay...

403
00:27:05,310 --> 00:27:09,480
That small knife is stopping
all of Zoro's three-sword-style attacks!

404
00:27:09,480 --> 00:27:12,360
He out-monsters
even the monstrous Zoro!

405
00:27:12,360 --> 00:27:13,860
I didn't...

406
00:27:13,860 --> 00:27:18,700
I didn't pursue swordsmanship all this time
to be a plaything for you and your toy!

407
00:27:24,160 --> 00:27:27,380
You're lucky, Zoro.
You were born a boy.

408
00:27:27,880 --> 00:27:31,670
I want to be the world's
greatest swordsman too!

409
00:27:32,170 --> 00:27:33,880
Promise me!

410
00:27:33,880 --> 00:27:38,550
Someday, one of us will be
the world's greatest swordsman!

411
00:27:38,550 --> 00:27:39,680
Promise me!

412
00:27:40,930 --> 00:27:41,930
– It's a promise!
– It's a promise!

413
00:27:47,480 --> 00:27:49,940
To become the world's greatest!

414
00:27:59,660 --> 00:28:04,160
I'll... get stronger
for the both of us now!

415
00:28:04,160 --> 00:28:06,830
I'll get so strong,
my name will reach the heavens!

416
00:28:06,830 --> 00:28:10,290
I'm gonna be the world's
greatest swordsman!

417
00:28:10,880 --> 00:28:12,670
I promised her...

418
00:28:12,670 --> 00:28:14,090
I...

419
00:28:23,350 --> 00:28:26,100
I did it all to defeat this man...

420
00:28:31,650 --> 00:28:32,980
What burden do you bear?

421
00:28:32,980 --> 00:28:37,280
What do you seek
in pursuing power, child?

422
00:28:37,360 --> 00:28:41,410
Your skill is most impressive.
Would you let us join you?

423
00:28:41,410 --> 00:28:45,450
We are bounty hunters, fearsome enough
to almost make your blood run cold,

424
00:28:45,450 --> 00:28:47,160
Yosaku and Johnny.

425
00:28:47,540 --> 00:28:50,420
Big Bro isn't a child, you cross creep!

426
00:28:50,420 --> 00:28:52,960
I'll teach you a lesson in manners...!

427
00:28:52,960 --> 00:28:55,840
Stop it, Yosaku and Johnny!
Don't get in his way!

428
00:28:56,300 --> 00:28:58,930
Be... patient...!

429
00:29:00,800 --> 00:29:02,550
Luffy...

430
00:29:03,850 --> 00:29:07,020
I... can't afford to lose...!

431
00:29:18,820 --> 00:29:19,950
Tiger...

432
00:29:19,950 --> 00:29:20,910
I like it!

433
00:29:20,910 --> 00:29:22,780
The world's greatest swordsman!

434
00:29:22,780 --> 00:29:26,410
That's exactly who the Pirate King
needs on his crew!

435
00:29:26,410 --> 00:29:27,500
Trap!

436
00:29:48,600 --> 00:29:51,520
Are you just going to let me
pierce your heart?

437
00:29:51,520 --> 00:29:53,270
Why aren't you withdrawing?

438
00:29:53,860 --> 00:29:56,110
I don't know why, but...

439
00:29:56,650 --> 00:29:58,740
if I withdraw even one step,

440
00:29:58,740 --> 00:30:05,240
it feels as if all the important oaths
and promises that I once made will shatter,

441
00:30:05,240 --> 00:30:08,700
and I won't be able to come
back to where I am now.

442
00:30:10,000 --> 00:30:12,120
Yes. That is defeat.

443
00:30:13,250 --> 00:30:15,540
Then, all the more reason
I can't withdraw...

444
00:30:16,340 --> 00:30:17,880
Even if you'll die?

445
00:30:18,670 --> 00:30:20,920
I'd rather die.

446
00:30:21,470 --> 00:30:24,010
What a strong heart!

447
00:30:24,010 --> 00:30:26,720
So he chooses death over defeat!

448
00:30:29,770 --> 00:30:31,770
Kid! State your name.

449
00:30:36,230 --> 00:30:38,230
Roronoa Zoro.

450
00:30:39,070 --> 00:30:40,490
I'll remember it.

451
00:30:40,490 --> 00:30:43,450
I've not met anyone like you
in a while, young man. Thus...

452
00:30:45,410 --> 00:30:50,580
as a swordsman's courtesy, I'll finish you
using the world's mightiest black blade.

453
00:30:50,580 --> 00:30:53,330
I appreciate it.

454
00:30:54,920 --> 00:30:55,920
He took it out!

455
00:30:55,920 --> 00:30:57,960
He sliced up the ship with that sword!

456
00:30:58,670 --> 00:31:01,170
So this will be the final attack...

457
00:31:01,170 --> 00:31:03,130
Will I rise to the world's greatest...

458
00:31:03,130 --> 00:31:04,130
or die?

459
00:31:08,550 --> 00:31:10,560
Big Bro! That's enough! Please stop!

460
00:31:10,560 --> 00:31:12,770
Three-Sword Style Secret Technique:

461
00:31:15,650 --> 00:31:16,560
Fall!

462
00:31:16,560 --> 00:31:18,940
Three Thousand Worlds!

463
00:31:26,280 --> 00:31:27,620
I lost...

464
00:31:29,120 --> 00:31:32,290
I never imagined I would lose...

465
00:31:34,080 --> 00:31:36,750
So this is the power
of the world's greatest...

466
00:31:40,750 --> 00:31:41,670
What are you...?

467
00:31:43,050 --> 00:31:45,550
Scars on the back
are a swordsman's shame...

468
00:31:46,010 --> 00:31:46,970
Superb!

469
00:31:50,850 --> 00:31:56,810
Zoro!

470
00:31:58,730 --> 00:32:01,610
Don't rush headlong
into the jaws of death, hotshot.

471
00:32:02,860 --> 00:32:04,240
Zoro!

472
00:32:05,360 --> 00:32:06,740
– Big Bro!
– Big Bro!

473
00:32:09,570 --> 00:32:11,080
Why?

474
00:32:13,370 --> 00:32:20,210
I threw my life away when I decided
to be the world's greatest swordsman.

475
00:32:22,000 --> 00:32:25,590
He's lost it! His opponent is
the actual greatest in the world!

476
00:32:26,510 --> 00:32:27,970
The outcome was obvious!

477
00:32:27,970 --> 00:32:30,180
Dying is worse than
giving up his ambition!

478
00:32:30,180 --> 00:32:31,510
The choice was easy!

479
00:32:31,510 --> 00:32:33,470
Just abandon your ambition!

480
00:32:37,060 --> 00:32:40,520
So this is the power of the Grand Line...
the power of the world!

481
00:32:41,110 --> 00:32:44,820
Pirate Hunter Zoro was
as helpless as a newborn!

482
00:32:44,820 --> 00:32:49,160
Damn you, damn you... damn you!

483
00:32:49,160 --> 00:32:51,120
– Big Bro!
– Big Bro!

484
00:32:55,700 --> 00:32:57,830
Wh-What did he just do?!

485
00:32:59,370 --> 00:33:03,340
So that brat has
the power of a devil fruit!

486
00:33:04,000 --> 00:33:04,880
You bast–

487
00:33:07,090 --> 00:33:09,630
Are you that young swordsman's comrade?

488
00:33:09,630 --> 00:33:12,470
You also impressed me
for bearing witness till the end.

489
00:33:16,850 --> 00:33:20,480
Have no fear. Today
is not the day he dies.

490
00:33:20,480 --> 00:33:21,230
Huh?

491
00:33:21,230 --> 00:33:23,980
Big Bro! Big Bro, say something!

492
00:33:23,980 --> 00:33:24,900
Zoro?!

493
00:33:26,860 --> 00:33:27,860
Zoro!

494
00:33:27,860 --> 00:33:29,780
Hurry, get him on the ship!

495
00:33:31,660 --> 00:33:33,410
Pour this medicine on him!

496
00:33:33,820 --> 00:33:36,240
It's still too early for you to die.

497
00:33:36,740 --> 00:33:39,370
My name is Dracule Mihawk!

498
00:33:39,370 --> 00:33:40,750
Learn about yourself!

499
00:33:40,750 --> 00:33:42,040
Learn about the world!

500
00:33:42,040 --> 00:33:43,330
And become strong!

501
00:33:43,330 --> 00:33:45,880
No matter how many years it takes,

502
00:33:45,880 --> 00:33:48,300
I'll await you with
the title of the greatest.

503
00:33:48,880 --> 00:33:51,050
Surpass this sword!

504
00:33:51,050 --> 00:33:55,430
Surpass me, Roronoa Zoro!

505
00:33:56,890 --> 00:33:59,640
Big Bro! Big Bro, say something!

506
00:33:58,140 --> 00:33:59,640
Big Bro!

507
00:34:00,430 --> 00:34:04,150
To think that he got
Hawk Eye Mihawk to say this much...

508
00:34:05,400 --> 00:34:07,900
Kid, what is your goal?

509
00:34:08,440 --> 00:34:09,530
King of the Pirates!

510
00:34:10,280 --> 00:34:14,280
That's a feat even more challenging
than surpassing me.

511
00:34:14,280 --> 00:34:17,030
How would I know,
when I haven't done it yet?!

512
00:34:18,120 --> 00:34:19,750
He's alive!

513
00:34:20,120 --> 00:34:21,500
He's just unconscious.

514
00:34:22,540 --> 00:34:24,670
Big Bro! Say something!

515
00:34:21,500 --> 00:34:22,540
Big Bro!

516
00:34:25,330 --> 00:34:26,420
Zoro?

517
00:34:27,090 --> 00:34:28,250
Big Bro!

518
00:34:29,760 --> 00:34:31,380
L... Luffy...

519
00:34:31,880 --> 00:34:33,130
Can you hear me?

520
00:34:33,130 --> 00:34:34,590
Yeah!

521
00:34:35,600 --> 00:34:37,760
Did I worry you?

522
00:34:38,760 --> 00:34:40,180
You'd struggle...

523
00:34:40,850 --> 00:34:46,690
with anything less than
the world's greatest swordsman, right?

524
00:34:47,690 --> 00:34:50,650
Big Bro! Please don't talk anymore!

525
00:34:49,570 --> 00:34:50,650
Big Bro!

526
00:34:51,110 --> 00:34:52,610
I...

527
00:34:52,990 --> 00:34:55,070
I will never...

528
00:34:55,070 --> 00:34:57,530
be defeated again!

529
00:35:00,240 --> 00:35:04,040
Until the day I defeat him
and become a master swordsman...

530
00:35:04,540 --> 00:35:06,000
I'll never...

531
00:35:06,000 --> 00:35:07,380
lose again!

532
00:35:08,040 --> 00:35:09,960
Got any problems with that...

533
00:35:11,380 --> 00:35:13,550
Pirate King?!

534
00:35:17,140 --> 00:35:18,140
Nope!

535
00:35:18,140 --> 00:35:19,930
You're a good team.

536
00:35:19,930 --> 00:35:22,850
I hope we cross paths again.

537
00:35:23,850 --> 00:35:25,980
Hey, Hawk Eye!

538
00:35:26,400 --> 00:35:29,900
Didn't you come to take my life,

539
00:35:29,900 --> 00:35:33,400
the life of Don Krieg,
conqueror of the East Blue?

540
00:35:33,860 --> 00:35:37,780
That was my intent,
but I've had my fill of fun.

541
00:35:37,780 --> 00:35:39,780
I'm heading home for some rest.

542
00:35:39,780 --> 00:35:43,500
You may have had your fill,
but I'm tired of losing to you.

543
00:35:43,500 --> 00:35:45,000
D-Don?

544
00:35:45,000 --> 00:35:47,380
Why are you trying
to keep him here?

545
00:35:47,750 --> 00:35:49,500
Here's a parting gift!

546
00:35:50,880 --> 00:35:53,130
It seems he still hasn't
learned his lesson...

547
00:36:01,140 --> 00:36:03,100
Damn! He escaped...

548
00:36:12,020 --> 00:36:13,690
Usopp!

549
00:36:13,690 --> 00:36:14,690
Luffy!

550
00:36:15,070 --> 00:36:17,410
Go! I'll leave Nami to you!

551
00:36:17,910 --> 00:36:18,910
Got it!

552
00:36:18,910 --> 00:36:21,830
Zoro and I will bring
Nami back for sure!

553
00:36:21,830 --> 00:36:24,370
You just get that cook
to join our crew!

554
00:36:24,750 --> 00:36:27,500
When all five of us
are reunited, let's go...

555
00:36:27,920 --> 00:36:29,920
to the Grand Line!

556
00:36:29,920 --> 00:36:30,920
Yeah!

557
00:36:30,920 --> 00:36:32,170
Sounds like a plan!

558
00:36:32,170 --> 00:36:37,340
Guys! We ran into some interference,
but the real fight starts now!

559
00:36:37,340 --> 00:36:39,010
We're taking that ship!

560
00:36:39,010 --> 00:36:40,140
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

561
00:36:40,140 --> 00:36:44,850
Boss Man, if I drive them off,
can I be done with chores?

562
00:36:44,850 --> 00:36:46,730
Be my guest.

563
00:21:25,060 --> 00:21:29,980
"Hawk Eye" Mihawk
The Greatest Swordsman
in the World

